<p>Most websites have zero backlinks. Not a few. Not a handful. Literally <a href="https://www.demandsage.com/link-building-statistics/">95% of all pages on the internet</a> have no external links pointing to them.</p>
<p>That is not a content problem. It is a link building problem. Specifically, it is a failure to find and act on the right link building opportunities.</p>
<p>This guide breaks down every major type of link building opportunity available in 2026. From broken link prospecting to HARO alternatives to competitor gap analysis, you will get exact steps for each method.</p>
<p>We publish 3,500+ blog posts across 70+ industries. We have watched what moves rankings and what does not. Backlinks still sit at the center of every ranking algorithm.</p>
<p>Here is what you will learn:</p>
<ul>
<li>How to find broken link building opportunities on authority sites</li>
<li>Where to pitch resource pages that actually link out</li>
<li>Which HARO alternatives still work after the 2024 shutdown</li>
<li>How to run a competitor backlink gap analysis</li>
